==English==

===Etymology===
From Hebrew [[אהרן|אַהֲרֹן]] ''(Ahărōn)'', "bearer of martyrs".

===Proper noun===

# A male [[given name]].
# A person in the [[Old Testament]], the elder brother of [[Moses]] in the Book of the [[Exodus]].

